  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid in response to Hurricam Disaster in the Central American countries - Guatemala, Honduras and Nicaragua</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The post-hurricane scenario in Honduras poses enormous challenges to the local and national authorities. In this regard the proposed action will focus on providing assistance to the displaced population through different actions and initiatives and supporting the national and local governments&#x2019; response. Through the proposed initiative, IOM is responding to the most urgent humanitarian needs of persons in communities and collective shelters in Honduras and particularly of those most vulnerable. The project prioritizes actions to ensure a minimum of privacy, comfort and the availability of psychosocial support and referral mechanisms to protection services for persons in shelters, particularly the most vulnerable. It also seeks to establish mobile teams and intersectoral coordination mechanisms to enhance the capacity and the provision of services of local shelters to crisis-affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
